cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language generation models and machine translation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a planning phase in neural machine translation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses an end-to-end neural network for the planning phase. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is possible as the paper deals with neural machine translation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses part-of-speech tags, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
